summary: [Image Description: A digital drawing of a black kobold, a race of creatures from DnD. He has a grey belly with a fire pattern,...
body:
[Image Description: A digital drawing of a black kobold, a race of creatures from DnD. He has a grey belly with a fire pattern, white tattoos on his inner thighs, clawed feet, large ears with three piercings on each, a tongue piercing, long fangs, horns along his head, down his back, and along his tail, and heterochromatic eyes, one green and one blue. He’s holding a quarterstaff in his hands. End Description]

I never uploaded a colored version of my current DnD character, so here he is!

His name is Ashbel “Ash” Firetooth, and he’s a Kobold multiclassed in Druid/Rogue/Cleric. I love playing him a lot!

blog.name: staceyjeanbarron
blog.title: Stacey Jean Barron
blog.description:
Life is a journey. One often gets lost and loses their path, and sometimes it is the materials, tools, artifacts & artefacts, totems, accouterments, and art-objects one has or finds along the way that best assist with the journey, and it's in that spirit Stacey Jean Barron posts her own art and the art of others.

Here are the beautiful findings, curious curios, collage epics, existential yearnings, nuggets of wisdom; the psycho-drama, the surreal, the cadaver exquis, the treasure at the end of the rainbow; the relic and the reliquary, the ruin and the re-used, the craft-ed and the art-ed.

Stacey is a maker, experimenter, dreamer, and thinker in the Oregon Willamette Valley, just south of downtown Portland. She collages, mixes media, arts-it-up, writes (not as much as she should), and guides students as a tutor.
